    <div class="card">
      <h2>Exploring Global Biodiversity</h2>
      <p>The natural world is teeming with an astonishing variety of life. This comprehensive <strong>list of animals</strong> serves as a gateway to understanding the incredible biodiversity found across different continents and oceans. From the deepest marine trenches to the highest mountain peaks, animals have evolved highly specialized physical and behavioral traits to survive and thrive in their unique environments.</p>

      <p>Understanding animal classification (taxonomy) helps scientists and enthusiasts alike organize the millions of known species. The primary biological classes highlighted here include Mammalia (mammals), Aves (birds), Reptilia (reptiles), Amphibia (amphibians), and various classes of fish and invertebrates. Each class represents a distinct evolutionary path, characterized by specific features such as warm or cold-blooded metabolism, methods of reproduction, and anatomical structures.</p>

      <p>Furthermore, an animal's diet is intrinsically linked to its ecological role. Carnivores maintain population balance by preying on herbivores, while herbivores shape plant communities through grazing and browsing. Omnivores exhibit immense adaptability, consuming a wide variety of food sources. The interactive directory below provides a detailed look at some of the world's most iconic, endangered, and peculiar species, complete with their taxonomic class, dietary classification, and estimated lifespans in the wild.</p>
